			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>Are you someone who is not afraid to pick-up the phone and cold-call an executive at a Fortune 500 company? Do you want to help the only Venture Capital backed bike sharing company in the world become the standard in bike sharing?</strong></p>
<p>
Zagster is currently hiring <strong>three </strong>Account Executives to help develop a national footprint of bike sharing programs in partnership with real estate/apartment companies, businesses, hotel chains and universities.</p>
<p>
The Account Executive team at Zagster is responsible for <strong>hunting </strong>and closing new business and inbound leads. This is a BIG role. You will be joining a very passionate team&nbsp; that has a work hard, play hard mentality. We need people who have sales experience and will &ldquo;step-up&rdquo; to manage the entire sales cycle. Someone who gets excited to be an early member of a team (we give equity!) that is continuing to build and refine the sales process.</p>
<p>
You consider yourself an <strong>entrepreneur</strong>. The role will be fluid and fast-paced, ranging from nitty-gritty research and legwork, to pitching executives from our&nbsp; clients, developing new business and defining a scalable and repeatable sales process. This is a <strong>rare opportunity</strong> to work directly with the CEO and executive team to increase your skill sets and grow your career.</p>
<p>
&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Become an expert, build out a pipeline and ultimately own the entire sales cycle from inception to closure within one of our key customer segments (real estate/apartment companies, businesses, hotel chains and universities)</li>
<li>
Juggle a lot of clients at once and keep all projects organized without letting anything slip through the cracks</li>
<li>
Prioritize leads through a qualification system that you will help create</li>
<li>
Close a lot of new accounts to allow Zagster to become the nationwide standard in bike sharing</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Requirements:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
1-2 years of hands-on sales experience as a &ldquo;hunter&rdquo; minimum</li>
<li>
Four year college degree in business or related field</li>
<li>
Motivated, self-starter, critical thinker and planner</li>
<li>
Excellent organization, presentation, and communication skills (verbal &amp; written)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Brownie Points:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Previous work experience with a startup company (a lot of brownie points for this one)</li>
<li>
Passion for sustainability and/or transportation</li>
<li>
You want to ride your bike to work everyday</li>
<li>
Experience selling to apartment complexes/management firms, hotels or universities</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Perks:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A brand new Fuji bike when you join our team!</li>
<li>
Monthly team outings (we recently played Paintball together)</li>
<li>
Flexible work schedule and a great T-accessible location</li>
<li>
Monthly health benefit (gym, personal training, etc.), health and dental insurance</li>
<li>
Opportunity to travel and explore new cities</li>
<li>
Competitive compensation and equity in a fast growth company</li>
</ul>
]]></description>
